  Locus:
    Page: 59
By: Mechthild of Magdeburg
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Separation-Sin=God’s Mercy
---
‘To whosoever is sorry for sin I forgive it and whoso yet laments his sin, to
him do I give My Grace. Whoso grieves for sin so that he would rather die than
sin again, shall after this life be condemned to no further punishment even
should he commit daily sins.’
